This is a XeLaTeX book project about the Kaappi Scheme programming language.

- Build: `make` (XeLaTeX, 3 passes). Quick: `make once`. Output: `build/main.pdf`
- Target audience: programmers who know Python but not Scheme
- Document class: memoir (11pt, twoside, openright)
- Fonts: EB Garamond (body), Source Sans 3 (headings), Fira Code (code)
- All packages and styles are in `preamble/`; never add packages in chapter files
- Chapter files live in `chapters/` and are included from `main.tex`
- Code examples use `\begin{lstlisting}` (Scheme syntax configured globally)
- Custom environments: `note`, `warning`, `exercise`, `codeoutput`
- Reference sources: `/Users/bmuthuka/kaappi/kaappi` (source), `/Users/bmuthuka/kaappi/kaappi.github.io` (docs)
- Write clearly for beginners; show runnable code; compare to Python when helpful
